"n. 事件的后果，余波 【英】 n.事件的后果，余波 (a unpleasant result or consequence) n. (尤指灾难或不幸)事件的后果, 余波; 灾后时期(灾难性事件后的一段时期) 【例】famine as an aftermath of drought 旱灾后是饥荒in the aftermath of war 战后时期 【记】after以后, ma拼: 马, th读: 死－马死以后. 在香港赌马特容易受骗. 我有一次根据《马经》精心挑选了的一匹""quot;阿伏特马嘶""quot;竟然在赛场上暴毙, 害的我损失惨重. 当然, 事情不会这样快的结束, 事件的后果、余波, 还有待进一步的追踪报导. 据说是有人赛假马! 【记】after + math = result，在数学（运算，处理）后会有什么？会得到结果 aftermath (n.)  1520s, originally a second crop of grass grown after the first had been harvested, from after + -math, a dialectal word, from Old English mæð ""a mowing, cutting of grass"" (see math (n.2)). Figurative sense by 1650s. Compare French regain ""aftermath,"" from re- + Old French gain, gaain ""grass which grows in meadows that have been mown,"" from a Germanic source similar to Old High German weida ""grass, pasture"""
